description:
Still continuing looking at old data and reprocess while waiting for things to setup in my new observatory. 

This data is from 2017 shot from my backyard my now-sold Edge11 and ASI1600 combination . The data is not as deep as I would like (5 min narrowband subs at unity gain). The calibration also left some edge artificats that I had to crop. However, the background etc was clear.

I processed in PI and tried a few different mapping of SHO data to see if I Can get some variation in the channels. It feels like there is a bit more data not resolving here (There is a super faint outcropping that I couldnt get to show up clearly) . I will revisit this again when the observatory is up and running.

Astrodon Ha 1.25 5nm: 36x300" bin 1x1
Astrodon OIII 1.25 3nm: 44x300" bin 1x1
Astrodon SII 1.25 5nm: 45x300" bin 1x1
title: M1 - SHO
